[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Right now, most AI coding agents rely on linear recursive discovery tools like grep, glob, and read to navigate a code base. This fan-out approach burns through token budgets and drives up latency. The agent is forced to execute'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a constant guess and check loop just to locate the right file long before it even reads the target logic. Code graph solves this by providing a local pre-indexed knowledge graph of your'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'entire code base. Using the model context protocol or MCP, this index is injected directly into the agent\'s workflow. Instead of executing a slow linear text search through thousands of'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'directories, the agent uses a deterministic graph retrieval. Across real-world benchmarks, this architectural shift cuts tool calls by 58%, reduces token usage by 47%, and drops latency by 22%. While raw LLM'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'context windows keep expanding, simply dumping massive amounts of unstructured text into them is a highly inefficient process. Refining the precision of context routing yields much faster, more'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'accurate performance. This data matrix compares an Opus 4.8 agent running with code graph versus one running without it. Let\'s isolate the rows for VS Code, a large 10,000 file TypeScript'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'repository, and Alamofire, a smaller 110 file Swift repository. Notice the file reads and grep columns. In both repositories, the baseline agent makes around 10 recursive calls just to'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'locate information. With code graph, that drops to exactly zero. Looking at the total tokens column, the Alamofire repository sees a 64% reduction in token consumption.'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This happens because a single code graph explore tool call bypasses the discovery phase entirely. It returns the required mechanism and exact path signatures in one structured payload.'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'To keep responses lean, redundant interchangeable implementations are collapsed down to their signatures. The payload size matches the complexity of the answer, rather than the file count of the repository.'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Because the read and grep discovery loop is removed, cost stays stable. It remains flat to cheaper across the board, whether the agent is scanning a massive monolith or a compact microservice.'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Eliminating that initial exploratory thrashing is the primary driver for optimizing an agent\'s token economy. To provide that deterministic local index, the raw source code has to be aggressively compiled into a queryable'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'format. Code graph uses tree-sitter to parse source files natively across more than 20 languages, transforming them into abstract syntax trees. Those extracted syntax nodes, like'

[02:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'functions and classes, along with their reference edges, are then populated directly into a relational SQLite database. On top of that relational schema sits an FTS5 full-text search integration layer. During the resolution'

[02:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'phase, the system connects those disparate reference edges, linking individual function calls back to their exact definitions anywhere in the repository. This filtering requires zero configuration. Language detection is'

[03:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'automatic, and common noise generators like node modules, build targets, and cache directories are excluded by default. By building a completely local SQLite schema, the agent can rely on highly deterministic code base state.'

[03:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This outperforms relying on remote vector embeddings, which lack structural precision. Traditional static analysis breaks down at multi-language boundaries and dynamic framework routing. The extraction simply halts when it hits a new runtime'

[03:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'environment. Code graph solves this through heuristic synthesis. If a Swift file invokes a method, an Objective-C auto bridging rule applies, and a connected edge is synthesized directly to the corresponding Objective-C'

[03:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'selector. That newly synthesized edge is explicitly tagged, so the agent knows exactly how the cross-language hop was made. This bridging maps dynamic URL patterns in web frameworks like Django or Express directly to their back-end'

[04:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'handler classes. In React Native architectures, it maps JavaScript native modules straight down to their underlying Java or Objective-C implementations. For the AI agent, this means it can'

[04:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'trace an accurate impact radius end-to-end, straight through a full-stack application. Providing these explicitly synthesized multi-language edges prevents the agent from hallucinating logic gaps when it tries to traverse complex enterprise'

[04:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'architectures. Even with perfect cross-language tracing, feeding an AI agent stale structural data while a developer is actively modifying code will cause hallucinations. Code graph integrates native OS file watchers like FS events'

[04:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and Inotify to instantly detect any source modifications. A 2,000-ms debounce window collapses bursts of developer edits into a single background re-index.'

[04:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If the AI agent attempts to query the graph during that brief debounce window, an MCP safeguard is triggered. The server intercepts the JSON tool response payload and prepends a yellow staleness banner.'

[05:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This banner explicitly instructs the agent to execute a standard direct file read for the live content of that specific file, ensuring it never operates on pending index data. If edits happen while the MCP server is offline, a connect time catch-up'

[05:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'protocol immediately reconciles file hashes the next time the agent connects. By combining OS-level watchers with explicit MCP-level staleness signaling, the agent\'s context is guaranteed to stay synchronized with the developer\'s'

[05:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'local state. Moving beyond the local pipeline, this marks a fundamental systemic transition in how AI agents interface with codebases today. Replacing unstructured text discovery with deterministic pre-indexed data'

[05:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'neutralizes exploratory hallucination entirely. That stability is built on three strict technical pillars: 100% local SQLite storage, heuristic cross-language bridging, and debounced'

[05:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'OS native syncing. Code graph enforces this with a restricted MCP tool set. By prioritizing the code graph explore tool, it actively steers agent behavior away from context trashing and into'

[06:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'immediate analysis. The result is a drastic reduction in total tool calls, overall token consumption, and wall clock latency. As models continue to advance, maximizing an agent\'s engineering'

[06:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'utility relies entirely on the precision of its context routing, rather than the raw capacity of its context window.'
